# We work with two sets:
nSets = 1;
# For easier labeling of plots, create a vector holding descriptive names of the two sets.
setLabels = c( "ovaries")
shortLabels = c("FBO")
# Form multi-set expression data: columns starting from 9 contain actual expression data.
ovaryExpr = vector(mode = "list", length = nSets)
###use ntd_brain, vst_brain,  rlog_brain, or common_brains
##use ntd_FBO, vst_FBO, rlog_FBO, or common_ovaries
ovaryExpr[[1]] = list(data=t(vst_all_FBO))
for(i in 1:nSets){
    ovaryExpr[[i]]$data<- apply(ovaryExpr[[i]]$data,2,as.numeric)
}
names(ovaryExpr[[1]]$data) <- rownames(vst_all_FBO)
rownames(ovaryExpr[[1]]$data) = colnames(vst_all_FBO)
exprSize = checkSets(ovaryExpr)
# Form a multi-set structure that will hold the clinical traits.
ovary_Traits = vector(mode="list", length = nSets);
for (set in 1:nSets)
{
setSamples = rownames(ovaryExpr[[set]]$data);
traitRows = match(setSamples, rownames(all_info));
ovary_Traits[[set]] = list(data = all_info[traitRows, ]);
rownames(ovary_Traits[[set]]$data) =rownames(all_info[traitRows, ]);
}
collectGarbage();
set.seed(10)
# Choose a set of soft-thresholding powers
powers = c(seq(4,10,by=1), seq(12,20, by=2));
# Initialize a list to hold the results of scale-free analysis
powerTables = vector(mode = "list", length = nSets);
# Call the network topology analysis function for each set in turn
for (set in 1:nSets)
powerTables[[set]] = list(data = pickSoftThreshold(ovaryExpr[[set]]$data, powerVector=powers,
verbose = 2)[[2]])

  {
    plot(powerTables[[set]]$data[,1], -sign(powerTables[[set]]$data[,3])*powerTables[[set]]$data[,2],

    addGrid();

    text(powerTables[[set]]$data[,1], powerTables[[set]]$data[,plotCols[col]],

  if (col==1)
  {
    legend("bottomright", legend = setLabels, col = colors, pch = 20) ;

load("../data/OvaryModules.RData")

##setup variables
nSets=1
moduleTraitCor_ovary = list();
moduleTraitPvalue_ovary = list();


# Calculate the correlations

for (set in 1:nSets){
    
res <- data.frame()
pvalues<-data.frame()
ME_names<-colnames(ovaryMEs[[1]]$data)

for (i in ME_names){
    print(i)
        
    trait_i<-ovary_Traits[[set]]$data
  test<-glm(ovaryMEs[[set]]$data[,i]~trait_i$MatxPat+
                trait_i$Block+
                trait_i$Rep_status)
  test%>%summary()%>%print()
  ##get coefficients
  coeff2<-coef(test)[2]
  coeff3<-coef(test)[3]
  coeff4<-coef(test)[4]
  coeff<-data.frame(MatxPat=coeff2,
                    Block=coeff3,
                    Rep_status=coeff4,
                    row.names = i)
  ##get pvalues
  pval2<-coef(summary(test))[2,4]
  pval3<-coef(summary(test))[3,4]
  pval4<-coef(summary(test))[4,4]
  pval<-data.frame(MatxPat=pval2,
                   Block=pval3,
                   Rep_status=pval4,
                   row.names = i)
  pvalues<-rbind(pvalues,pval)
  res<-rbind(res,coeff)
  }
moduleTraitCor_ovary[[set]]<-res
moduleTraitPvalue_ovary[[set]]<-pvalues
}
###Build consensus figure
 heat.col<-viridis(100)

# Initialize matrices to hold the consensus correlation and p-value
OvaryCor = matrix(NA, nrow(moduleTraitCor_ovary[[1]]), ncol(moduleTraitCor_ovary[[1]]));
OvaryPvalue = matrix(NA, nrow(moduleTraitCor_ovary[[1]]), ncol(moduleTraitCor_ovary[[1]]));
# Find consensus negative correlations
negative = moduleTraitCor_ovary[[1]] < 0 
OvaryCor[negative] = pmax(moduleTraitCor_ovary[[1]][negative]);
OvaryPvalue[negative] = pmax(moduleTraitPvalue_ovary[[1]][negative]);
# Find consensus positive correlations
positive = moduleTraitCor_ovary[[1]] > 0 
OvaryCor[positive] = pmin(moduleTraitCor_ovary[[1]][positive]);
OvaryPvalue[positive] = pmax(moduleTraitPvalue_ovary[[1]][positive]);
##plotting consensus figure

##only display those that are significant
display<-pmap_dfr(OvaryPvalue,~data.frame(min_MatxPat=..1>0.05 , min_Block=..2>0.05 , min_Rep=..3>0.05))

ME_names<-colnames(consMEs[[set]]$data)

for (i in ME_names){
    print(i)
        
    trait_i<-Traits[[set]]$data
  test<-glm(consMEs[[set]]$data[,i]~trait_i$MatxPat+
                trait_i$Block+
                trait_i$Rep_status)
  test%>%summary()%>%print()
  ##get coefficients
  coeff2<-coef(test)[2]
  coeff3<-coef(test)[3]
  coeff4<-coef(test)[4]
  coeff<-data.frame(MatxPat=coeff2,
                    Block=coeff3,
                    Rep_status=coeff4,
                    row.names = i)
  ##get pvalues
  pval2<-coef(summary(test))[2,4]
  pval3<-coef(summary(test))[3,4]
  pval4<-coef(summary(test))[4,4]
  pval<-data.frame(MatxPat=pval2,
                   Block=pval3,
                   Rep_status=pval4,
                   row.names = i)
  pvalues<-rbind(pvalues,pval)
  res<-rbind(res,coeff)
  }
moduleTraitCor[[set]]<-res
moduleTraitPvalue[[set]]<-pvalues
}

# Isolate the module labels in the order they appear in ordered module eigengenes

ovaModuleLabels = substring(names(ovaryMEs[[1]]$data), 3)
consModuleLabels = substring(names(consMEs[[3]]$data), 3)

# Convert the numeric module labels to color labels
ovaModules = labels2colors(as.numeric(ovaModuleLabels))
consModules = labels2colors(as.numeric(consModuleLabels))

# Numbers of female and consensus modules
nOVAMods = length(ovaModules)
nConsMods = length(consModules)

# Initialize tables of p-values and of the corresponding counts
pTable = matrix(0, nrow = nOVAMods, ncol = nConsMods);
CountTbl = matrix(0, nrow = nOVAMods, ncol = nConsMods);
# Execute all pairwaise comparisons
for (omod in 1:nOVAMods)
for (cmod in 1:nConsMods)
{
ovaMembers = (ovaryMColors == ovaModules[omod]);
consMembers = (consMColors == consModules[cmod]);
pTable[omod, cmod] = -log10(fisher.test(ovaMembers, consMembers, alternative = "greater")$p.value);
CountTbl[omod, cmod] = sum(ovaryMColors == ovaModules[omod] & consMColors ==
consModules[cmod])
}

# Truncate p values smaller than 10^{-50} to 10^{-50}
pTable[is.infinite(pTable)] = 1.3*max(pTable[is.finite(pTable)]);
pTable[pTable>50 ] = 50 ;
# Marginal counts (really module sizes)
ovaModTotals = apply(CountTbl, 1, sum)
consModTotals = apply(CountTbl, 2, sum)

# Calculate the correlations

for (set in 1:nSets){
    
res <- data.frame()
pvalues<-data.frame()
ME_names<-colnames(consMEs[[set]]$data)

for (i in ME_names){
  print(i)
    trait_i<-Traits[[set]]$data
  test<-glm(consMEs[[set]]$data[,i]~trait_i$MatxPat+
                trait_i$Allele+
                trait_i$Block)
  test%>%summary()%>%print()
  ##get coefficients
  coeff2<-coef(test)[2]
  coeff3<-coef(test)[3]
  coeff4<-coef(test)[4]
  coeff<-data.frame(MatxPat=coeff2,
                    Allele=coeff3,
                    Block=coeff4,
                    row.names = i)
  ##get pvalues
  pval2<-coef(summary(test))[2,4]
  pval3<-coef(summary(test))[3,4]
  pval4<-coef(summary(test))[4,4]
  pval<-data.frame(MatxPat=pval2,
                   Allele=pval3,
                   Block=pval4, 
                   row.names = i)
  pvalues<-rbind(pvalues,pval)
  res<-rbind(res,coeff)
  

  }
moduleTraitCor[[set]]<-res
moduleTraitPvalue[[set]]<-pvalues
}
